column18: 03/30/2007: A Sudan Airways plane was hijacked while enroute from Libya by a knife wielding Sudanese assailant.  The plane was diverted and landed safely in Khartoum Airport.  No group claimed responsibility.
column126: Edward F. Mickolus, Terrorism, 2005-2007: A Chronology  (Westport, CT: Praeger Security International) 2008.

column17: The plane landed at Al Kufrah Airport in Kufrah, Libya.
column18: 08/26/2008: On Tuesday, at 1800, three members of the Sudanese Liberation Movement hijacked Sun Air flight 611 en route to Khartoum. The plane, which had a total of 95 passenger on board, landed at 1940 at Al Kufrah airport in Kufrah, Libya. No casualties were reported and two hijackers surrendered.
column64: The specific motive for the attack is unknown.
column97: A knife was used in the attack.
